it sounds like you want to implement &quot;toggle&quot; and i doubt &quot;toggle&quot; would
ever be idempotent since idempotent requests will contain the state that
you want to write (&quot;on&quot; or &quot;off&quot;).

FWIW, you could use a non-idempotent write (HTTP.POST) to implement
&quot;toggle&quot; -- that would be consistent at the *network level* -- but i&#39;m not
sure if that&#39;s what you need.




